SESSION.DESCRIPTION: This session can be used to get date ranges for certain period types. It uses the VRAP.VRCIT_MODEL_PRD_STUS view, and you pass in the CLM_LOCK_CD and APC_STAT_CD values. It puts out the MIN/MAX Quarter period and Monthly periods, along with their associated Start and End dates, based on what values you pass in. Since it builds a Parameter file for use in another session, you also need to pass in the Folder, Workflow, and the Worklet or Session that will be using the new Parameter file.
SESSION.NAME: s_m_Get_Period_Dt_Ranges

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This SQ will use the BCI table to get good, open and closed period claims. It will then join the BCI table to the BCA table to get a few fields from BCA for the Finance Summary table. The SQ uses input parameters to choose the appropriate periods, and also apply dates to the INV_ELIG_DT.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: sq_Open_Closed_nonAPC_Locked_period_GOOD_clms

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: User Defined Join
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
--Joins VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_APC.CLM_GID = VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV.CLM_GID
AND VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV.PRD_ID = VRAP.VRCIT_MODEL_PRD_STUS.PRD_ID AND VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV.MODEL_TYP_CD = VRAP.VRCIT_MODEL_PRD_STUS.MODEL_TYP_CD

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Source Filter
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: --Filters VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV.INV_ELIG_DT BETWEEN $$MIN_MTH_STRT_DT AND $$MAX_MTH_END_DT AND VRAP.VRCIT_MODEL_PRD_STUS.CLM_LOCK_CD IN ($$CLM_LOCK_CD) -- Closed or Open periods AND VRAP.VRCIT_MODEL_PRD_STUS.APC_STAT_CD IN ($$APC_STAT_CD) -- APC is open AND VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV.NRE_CLM_CD = '0' -- good claim AND VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV.RBEL_CLNT_CD = '1' -- Client is Rebate Eligible

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This SQ will use the BCI table to get good, open and closed period claims. It will then join the BCI table to the BCA table to get a few fields from BCA for the Finance Summary table. The SQ uses input parameters to choose the appropriate periods, and also apply dates to the INV_ELIG_DT.
INSTANCE.NAME: sq_Open_Closed_nonAPC_Locked_period_GOOD_clms
